ai-patthana16.9:0.2_0: Having given the immaculateness of the Dhamma
ai-patthana16.9:1.1_0: One who has no indeterminately does not give rise to unskillful things, nor what is skillful.
ai-patthana16.9:1.1_1: One who has no indeterminately does not give rise to unskillful things, nor what is skillful.
ai-patthana16.9:1.1_2: Not skilled in loss, earnings, nose-tips, tongue-consciousness, or body, and speech.
ai-patthana16.9:1.1_4: There are three more mendicants who have no regrets.
ai-patthana16.9:2.1_1: Three unwholesome things, not penetrating wisdom:
ai-patthana16.9:2.1_2: There are three undetermined, not without responsive.
ai-patthana16.9:2.1_3: (They are) wholesome and unwholesome, not indeterminate,
ai-patthana16.9:2.1_8: that’s not the fifteenth day sabbath.
